# Discord Chat Analysis

## 1. Summary
The discussion primarily revolves around ElizaOS's recent challenges with X (Twitter) and upcoming developments. Shaw confirmed that their X account was suspended, likely due to concerns about data scraping. They've submitted clarification that they don't scrape or sell X data and are awaiting account restoration. Shaw also mentioned that V2 is complete and ready to be announced once their accounts are restored. There was discussion about X's new API pricing ($50k/month) making it prohibitively expensive for many AI agent developers. A community member (z1) claimed to have developed a scraper that bypasses the official API but warned about potential detection. DorianD proposed a decentralized network concept where numerous Eliza Nodes could scrape X and store data in encrypted vaults with vectorization to avoid legal issues. Shaw hinted at "big breakthroughs in capability" coming soon and mentioned building a presence on Farcaster as an alternative platform.

## 2. FAQ
Q: When will version 2 be released? (asked by ghk9698) A: "V2 is done and shipped and we'll announce it when we get the accounts back" (answered by shaw)
Q: When will X account be back? (asked by ghk9698) A: Shaw thinks it will return after they filled out a questionnaire clarifying they don't scrape or sell X data (answered by Odilitime and shaw)
Q: What happened to agent-twitter-client repo? (asked by SajidBanday) A: It's been taken offline, guessing X asked them to remove it (answered by Odilitime)
Q: What's the best way of getting in touch with the ai16z dao team? (asked by cwm) A: Unanswered

## 3. Help Interactions
Helper: cjft | Helpee: General community | Context: How to install ElizaOS | Resolution: Shared installation command "npm i -g @elizaos/cli && elizaos create" with link to v1.0.10 release
Helper: shaw | Helpee: phetrusrodrigues and community | Context: Concerns about X account suspension and FUD | Resolution: Explained they're working on it and have submitted required information to X

## 4. Action Items
Type: Technical | Description: Develop decentralized network for X data scraping with encrypted vaults and vectorization | Mentioned By: DorianD
Type: Technical | Description: Complete benchmarks for new capability breakthroughs | Mentioned By: shaw
Type: Feature | Description: Build presence on Farcaster as alternative platform | Mentioned By: shaw
Type: Documentation | Description: Create guide for agent creation (requested indirectly) | Mentioned By: digitalalchemy

# Discord Chat Analysis for ðŸ’»-tech-support

## 1. Summary:
The chat primarily revolves around ElizaOS framework implementation issues and setup challenges. Users are discussing the latest version (v1.0.10/v1.0.11) and experiencing various technical problems. One user (Devansh) encountered a persistent error related to JSON parsing and module imports when trying to set up ElizaOS. The error specifically involves the pg module's Pool export not being properly recognized. Another user inquired about building an agent for crypto market insights, and received guidance about available plugins like pyth, coinmarketcap, and coingecko. There was also a brief discussion about architecture considerations for keeping agents lean by separating backend processing. The community appears active in troubleshooting issues, with members attempting to help each other resolve technical problems.

## 2. FAQ:
Q: Would it be viable to have a separate backend for the providers, especially for multi-step processes that requires pubsub/coordinating different services? (asked by orayo) A: Unanswered
Q: I want to build an agent that's aware of market prices and can post crypto insights. Could you tell me what tools I should use or where to start? (asked by Jon) A: With regards to where to start, the quickstart in eliza.how is a good 0-1 starting point. We are currently on 1.0.9 within the framework and some of the plugins have not yet been migrated but within the plugin directory you will see availability of market data like pyth, coinmarket cap, coingeko. (answered by Kenk)
Q: Am I the only one having issues with the new plugin-twitter? It just does nothing even and yes I changed my logins to the twitter api credentials (asked by lord_dubious) A: Unanswered
Q: Is hoplite role, still 100k Degenai? (asked by Dr. Neuro) A: Unanswered

## 3. Help Interactions:

Helper: sayonara | Helpee: Devansh | Context: User experiencing "Text is not JSON" error and module import issues | Resolution: Suggested using latest ElizaOS version (v1.0.11) and alternative installation methods using Bun, but issue remained unresolved
